{
  "stem": "26765.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You know, when these big transports would go, and the children would go, and you know, the mothers would go, and the father-- all the fathers were somewhere else.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I would see the people being loaded onto open trucks, and they would sing.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They would sing.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And that amazed me so much.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They would sing a, a Dutch song.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It went-- it was popular at the time-- [NON-ENGLISH], Oh, I wish it were true, then I would have happiness in my life.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And then, they sang the song, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And of course, that memory has stayed with me, and it has, it just has been a revelation to me about these people who were there in the camp with us, the adults.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I never had the additional fear that these adults had, about the crematoriums and about what might happen.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I never thought that we would get killed.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I had no idea about the crematorium.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I did not have those fears.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Not from beginning to end did I ever think we would not survive.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But the adults had that additional fear, along with the hunger, the starvation, the, the cold, the heat, the constant itching from lice, the sickness, the diarrhea, the filth, the humiliation.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They had that fear.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I am just amazed at these people, my fellow Jews, because I was there as a child.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I was there from eight to 10 in the concentration camp with absolutely starving people.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "They never took my piece of bread from me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "No one ever molested me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "No one ever hit me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "There was always someone who looked after us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Then in-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Shortly thereafter, we also were sent to Westerbork.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "This is another camp in Holland.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And in Westerbork, we were in an orphanage.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
